title: Welcome to Data Woman
text: I’m a data scientist passionate about leveraging data and AI to solve real-world problems. With expertise spanning organizational data science, artificial intelligence applications in scientific research, and cutting-edge technology tools, I help bridge the gap between data and decision-making.

title: Welcome to Data Woman
text:
About Me
I specialize in making data accessible, actionable, and impactful. Whether it’s building data pipelines for organizations, applying machine learning to scientific challenges, or exploring the latest tools in the data ecosystem, I’m driven by curiosity and a commitment to excellence.
My work sits at the intersection of technology, strategy, and science. I believe that good data science isn’t just about algorithms—it’s about understanding the problem, communicating insights clearly, and building solutions that actually work in the real world.

title: Welcome to Data Woman
text:
What I’m Interested In
Data Science in Organizations - Building data cultures, establishing best practices, and creating scalable analytics solutions that drive business value.
AI for Science - Applying machine learning and AI techniques to accelerate scientific discovery and research across domains.
Tech Tools - Exploring and mastering the evolving landscape of data science tools, from Python libraries to cloud platforms and everything in between.

title: Welcome to Data Woman
text:
Let’s Connect
I’m always interested in connecting with fellow data enthusiasts, researchers, and professionals. Feel free to reach out through any of the channels above—I’d love to hear from you!
